com.ibm.ecm.api.coresdk.model

Interface IBMECMSyncChange

  • All Superinterfaces:
    Comparable<IBMECMBaseObject>, IBMECMBaseObject, Serializable

    public interface IBMECMSyncChange
extends IBMECMBaseObject
    Represents a change that occurs on an item during a sync process.

    You can grab the list of changes from the last sync run by calling getAttributes().

    • Method Summary

      All Methods Instance Methods Abstract Methods 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      Map<String,Object> getAttributes()
      Returns the attributes that changed from the last sync process.
      String getObjectId()
      Returns the object id for this sync change.
      String getVSId()
      Returns the vs id for the item of this sync change.
      boolean isFolder()
      Returns whether this item of the sync change is a folder.
      boolean isHandled()
      Returns whether this sync change has been handled.
      boolean isSyncItemChange()
      Returns this change was for a sync item.
